###############################################################################
# OBJECTIVE
###############################################################################
Implement request throttling mechanism to prevent infinite API calls in tracking player
that broke the server. Protect server from rapid repeated requests.

###############################################################################
# REQUIREMENTS
###############################################################################
requirements:
  - Create API request throttler/debouncer utility with configurable delay
  - Apply throttling to tracking player API calls (position updates, frame navigation)
  - Implement request deduplication to prevent identical concurrent requests
  - Add visual feedback when requests are throttled
  - Log throttled requests for debugging
  - Ensure critical requests still pass through appropriately
  - Use existing store API methods rather than direct getApiClient calls

###############################################################################
# DELIVERABLES
###############################################################################
out: [API request throttling system]
done:
  - Tracking player no longer floods server with requests
  - Throttling utility reusable across application
  - Server protected from API abuse
  - User experience remains responsive
ref: @navitrack-apps/src-client/CODE_MAP.md (API layer); store methods.
